The paper discusses the use of multipath technology in computer networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the control plane problem and data plane problem, which are both related to network security (cs.CR). The use of multipath technology in data center computing is also mentioned, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the development and standardization of multipath transport protocols, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper highlights open issues and identifies directions for future work, which is related to social and information networks (cs.SI).
